	Providence Equity Partners Raises $2.8 Billion Fund
	mail this story? top
	
	PROVIDENCE, R.I. (VENTUREWIRE) -- Providence Equity Partners, a private 
equity investment firm with offices in Providence, R.I., and London said it 
closed a  $2.8 billion Fund IV in November. The fund was raised from the 
firm's existing limited partners. Focusing on telecommunications and media 
companies, Providence Equity Partners will commit between $25 million and 
$200 million to each of its portfolio companies and will invest across all 
development stages. Its past private equity investments include Mpower 
Communications, Tele1 Europe Holding A.B., Verio, Brooks Fiber Properties, 
and Western Wireless.  
	http://www.provequity.com
	
	
	Insight Capital Partners Raising $750 Million Fund
	mail this story? top
	
	NEW YORK (VENTUREWIRE) -- At an industry conference in New York, Jerry 
Murdock, co-founding partner of Insight Capital Partners, said the firm was 
raaising its fourth fund, worth $750 million. A spokesperson for the firm 
said that the fund's final closing is slated for early next year, and it has 
already begun deploying the funds. Details about the investments weren't 
disclosed. 
	http://www.insightpartners.com
	
	
	Optical Technology Firm Caspian Gets $85 Million
	mail this story? top
	
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (VENTUREWIRE) -- Caspian Networks, a company that is 
building technology for service providers' optical networks, said it raised 
$85 milllion in its third round of funding. Merrill Lynch, H&Q Asia Pacific, 
SSB Capital Partners, ABN AMRO Private Equity, Global Technology Group 
Ventures, Acute Communications and i100 Optical Asia are new investors in the 
round. Previous investors participating in this round were U.S. Venture 
Partners, New Enterprise Associates, Lucent Venture Partners, WorldCom 
Ventures, Vulcan Ventures, Alloy Ventures, and Applied Technologies. 
Individual investors Nicholas Negroponte and Leonard Kleinrock also invested. 
With this round, the company has raised $140 million to date. The company 
added a board seat and an observer board seat.
	http://www.caspiannetworks.com
	
	
	Technologic Partners Names Top Ten at Technology Outlook
	mail this story? top
	
	SAN FRANCISCO (VENTUREWIRE) -- Technologic Partners, which publishes 
VentureWire, named the top ten Investors' Choice companies at its Technology 
Outllook conference. The winners were chosen by conference attendees and a 
panel of industry observers that included William Cockayne, director of Kodak 
Venture Division; William A. Frezza, general partner with Adams Capital 
Management; Seth Goldstein, principal of Flatirion Partners; and Mark H. 
Sherman, general partner with Battery Ventures. The ten winners, in 
alphabetical order, are 2Wire, AlterEgo Networks, Atheros Communications, 
Entropia, MobileAria, PacketVideo, Silicon Wave, Tresidder Networks, United 
Devices, and ViaFone.
	http://www.technologicpartners.com
	
	
