	PacketVideo Raising Round for Up to $100 Million 
	mail this story? top
	
	SAN FRANCISCO (VENTUREWIRE) -- PacketVideo, which provides wireless 
multimedia software and services for mobile applications, is raising a Series 
E round  of new funding, which it expects to close between $80 million and 
$100 million by January. PacketVideo raised a $16.5 million Series D round 
this past May. The company is backed by Credit Suisse First Boston, Intel, 
Nexus Group, Qualcomm, Reuters, Royal Philips Electronics, Siemens Mustang 
Ventures, the Rockefeller family, Sonera Venture Capital, Sony, Texas 
Instruments, Time Warner, and others.   
	http://www.packetvideo.com
	
	
	Benefits App Firm BISnet Raises $2 Million in Series A
	mail this story? top
	
	CONCORD, Calif. (VENTUREWIRE) -- BISnet, which develops employee benefit 
enrollment and administration applications and software for mid-size and 
large comppanies, said Colonial Life and Accident Insurance Co. has invested 
$2 million as part of the company's still-open Series A round of financing. 
This investment brings the total amount raised to date from undisclosed 
individuals and strategic partners to $4.2 million. The company seeks an 
additional $5.8 million and said it will use the funds to increase sales.    
	http://www.bisnet.com
	
	
	IP Firm Mediatrix Telecom Closes $14.5 Million First Round
	mail this story? top
	
	MONTREAL (VENTUREWIRE) -- Mediatrix, a supplier of Internet protocol service 
applications, signaling software stacks, server software, and intelligennt 
communication devices including access and trunking gateways, said it has 
closed a $14.5 million first round of financing. Mustang Ventures, the 
venture arm of Siemen's Information and Communication Networking groups, as 
well as other undisclosed investors, participated in the round. The company 
said it will use the funds to develop and commercialize its applications.   
	http://www.mediatrix.com
	
	
	Wireless ASP GiantBear Secures $25 Million in Series B
	mail this story? top
	
	WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. (VENTUREWIRE) -- GiantBear, a wireless application service 
provider, said it has secured $25 million in its Series B round of funding 
led byy First Union Capital Partners that included previous investors, Thomas 
H. Lee Partners and Blackstone Capital Partners. The company said it will use 
the funds to develop its technology and expand market reach. Sean Smith of 
First Union Capital Partners will join GiantBear's board of directors.    
	http://www.giantbear.com
	
	
	Distributed Computing Firm Simulant Raises $400,000 Seed
	mail this story? top
	
	PASADENA, Calif. (VENTUREWIRE) -- Simulant, which has developed software to 
network computers together for processing power equal to that of 
supercomputers,  said it has raised $400,000 in a seed funding from ITU 
Ventures, a venture capital firm that finances businesses emerging from 
graduate universities. The company was founded by professor Axel Scherer and 
students Tom Baehr-Jones and Michael Hochberg from the California Institute 
of Technology. The company said it will use the funds for working capital and 
for business and product development.    
	http://www.simulant.com
	
	
	United Devices Looking for $25 Million in Series B Funding
	mail this story? top
	
	SAN FRANCISCO (VENTUREWIRE) -- Austin, Texas-based United Devices, which 
develops and manages Internet distributed computing technology, said it was 
lookiing to raise between $20 million and $25 million in a Series B round of 
funding to close by March of 2001. The company said it would use the funding 
to recruit additional senior management, product development, and for sales 
and marketing. United Devices closed its Series A round in August with $13 
million and is backed by Oak Investment Partners, Softbank Venture Capital, 
and others.
	http://www.ud.com
	
	
	Consulting Firm Quidnunc Lands $14.5 Million in Round Two
	mail this story? top
	
	NEW YORK (VENTUREWIRE) -- Quidnunc, an international digital business 
consulting firm, said it has secured $14.5 million in its second round of 
fundiing led by Barclays Ventures. The round also included Weston Presido 
Capital, Goldman Sachs Private Equity Partners, and Pi Capital. The company 
said it will use the funds to develop its international infrastructure. The 
company raised $15 million in its first round over a year ago.    
	http://www.quidnunc.com
	
	
	Exec Benefits Firm Rivenet Raises $8 Million Series B
	mail this story? top
	
	CHICAGO (VENTUREWIRE) -- Rivenet, an online company that automates the 
design, implementation, and administration of non-qualified benefit plans 
forr executives, said it has raised $8 million in its Series B round from 
co-leads William Blair New World Ventures and Lunn Partners. Adam Schecter, a 
principle of William Blair New World Ventures, and Robert Lunn, a managing 
partner of Lunn Partners, will join Rivenet's board as the fourth and fifth 
members. The company said it will use the funds to develop its technology and 
to form partnerships with the insurance and executive benefits industries.   
	http://www.rivenet.com
	
	
	Mobile Game Firm In-Fusio Raises $11.5 Million Round Two
	mail this story? top
	
	BORDEAUX, France  (VENTUREWIRE) -- In-Fusio, a supplier of connected mobile 
game services to telecom mobile operators, said it received GBP 8 million 
($11.5 mmillion) in its second round of funding. Banexi Ventures, Codexi, 
Expanso, Natio Vie et D,veloppement III, Partech, and Viventures participated 
in the round. In-Fusio said it will use the funds to continue its product 
development and strengthen its international expansion into Europe and Asia. 
The company's ExEn technology allows games to be downloaded from a server 
onto mobile phones. In-Fusio received  nearly $1.9 million in its first round 
from Banexi Ventures in 1999.  
	http://www.in-fusio.com
	
	
	Platform Developer Advent Has $22.6 Million Round Two
	mail this story? top
	
	AUSTIN, Texas. (VENTUREWIRE) -- Advent Networks, which is developing a 
platform for high-bandwidth delivery, said it has secured $22.6 million in 
its seconnd round of funding led by UtiliCorp United, an energy company. 
Other investors include Southern Union Company, which already holds an 11% 
stake in Advent, Motorola, Reliant Energy, Murphree Venture Partners, and 
Morgan Keegan & Co. The company said it will use the funds to develop its 
technology.     
	http://www.adventnetworks.com
	
	
	The Iris Group Raises $2.23 Million in Round Two
	mail this story? top
	
	DUBLIN (VENTUREWIRE) -- The Iris Group, a geographic data and technology 
company, said it has secured EUR 2.5 million ($2.23 million) in its secondd 
round of funding from Merrion Capital, Trinity Venture Capital, and 
individual investors. The company said it will use the funds to support the 
growth of Mapflow, its new Internet and wireless technology unit. Mapflow is 
focused on technology that would pinpoint the location of the wireless user 
and make it easier for the user to download Internet content specific to 
their location. 
	http://www.iris-gis.com
	
	
	Israeli IP Technology Firm Xpert Gets $15 Million
	mail this story? top
	
	JERUSALEM (VENTUREWIRE) -- Xpert, a provider of architecture design and 
implementation for IP-based service providers, said it received $15 million 
frrom Israel Seed Partners, CDB WebTech, and previous investeor 
Ampal-American Israel. The company will use the funds for its European 
expansion. Michael Eisenberg, general partner at Israel Seed, will join the 
company's board of directors. 
	http://www.xpert.com
	
	
	YourEnergySource Buys Stake in B2B Marketplace CheMatch.com
	mail this story? top
	
	HOUSTON (VENTUREWIRE) -- CheMatch.com, a business-to-business Internet-based 
marketplace for buyers and sellers of bulk commodity chemicals, plasticcs and 
fuel products, and YourEnergySource, a wholly owned subsidiary of Aquila 
Energy Corp., announced that YourEnergySource has made an equity investment 
in CheMatch.com. Last month CheMatch laid off eight employees but said at the 
time it expected more funding. The two companies also formed a strategic 
alliance which enables CheMatch.com customers to negotiate for power and 
natural gas contracts online on YourEnergySource's RFP Marketplace. 
YourEnergySource operates a digital energy marketplace. CheMatch is backed by 
Battery Ventures, Bayer, Computer Sciences Corp., E.E. DuPont de Nemours & 
Co., Methanex, Millennium Chemicals, H. Muehlstein & Co., Reed Elsevier, 
Sprout Group, Stolt-Nielsen, and TownsendTarnell. 
	http://www.chematch.com
	http://www.yourenergysource.com 
	
	
	Patient Data Firm InfoMedics Raises $10 Million F Round
	mail this story? top
	
	WOBURN, Mass. (VENTUREWIRE) -- InfoMedics, a provider of experimental patient 
data for the pharmaceutical industry, said it closed a $10 million Series F  
round of financing. Merrill Lynch Ventures and previous investors Sutter Hill 
Ventures, North Bridge Venture Partners, UnitedHealth Care's Validus, and 
Johnson & Johnson Development participated in the round. The company said it 
will use the funds to support growth and worldwide expansion of the company, 
and to further new product development. InfoMedics documents patients' 
experiences with pharmaceutical and over-the-counter products, and provides 
experimential patient data back to prescribing physicians and pharmaceutical 
companies. The company has raised $25 million to date.  
	http://www.infomedics.com
	
	
	Stock Quote ASP Money.net Closes Series C Led by Mitsubishi
	mail this story? top
	
	NEW YORK (VENTUREWIRE) -- Money.net, a hosted, streaming, real-time market 
data ASP, said it closed a Series C round of financing led by Mitsubishi aat 
an undisclosed amount. Other investors in the round were not disclosed. The 
company said it would use the funds to enhance its streaming technology and 
expand its ASP licensing business. A member of Mitsubishi will join 
Money.net's board of directors. The company is also backed by C. Blair Asset 
Management. 
	http://www.money.net
	
	
	3Com Ventures Takes Stake in Fitness Tech Firm HealtheTech
	mail this story? top
	
	SANTA CLARA, Calif. (VENTUREWIRE) -- 3Com Ventures announced that it took an 
undisclosed stake in HealtheTech, a provider of consumer health monitoring 
technoloogy. HealtheTech will provide a new health channel on 3Com's Internet 
appliance, Audrey, which will give consumers access to HealtheTech's Web 
service. 3Com will receive a revenue share on service subscriptions and the 
sale of HealtheTech products and devices bought by Audrey users. HealtheTech 
has received funding from Palm Ventures and Proctor & Gamble. 
	http://www.healthetech.com
	
	
