	STOCKHOLM (VENTUREWIRE) -- Stonepath Europe, a joint venture of Stonepath 
Group, said it invested $450,000 in Trade Extensions, a company that 
developps software for streamlining  online auction platforms. 
	http://www.tradeextensions.com
	
	
	bad news
	?
	HarvardNet Cuts Staff, Shuts Down DSL Connection Services
	mail this story? top
	
	MEDFORD, Mass.  (VENTUREWIRE) -- HarvardNet, which provided DSL and Web 
hosting services, said it is cutting its staff by 280 employees and halting 
its DSL  operations. The company said it will concentrate on its Web hosting 
and managed services business. Mark Washburn, president and CEO of 
HarvardNet, said, "The DSL business is very capital intensive and the recent 
dramatic downturn in the financial markets makes it difficult to continue 
offering DSL services." HarvardNet is offering a severance package, 
outplacement counseling, and a job fair for the employees affected by the 
restructuring. The company had raised $70 million in its second round of 
funding from investors including the Sturm Group, Vulcan Ventures, Fidelity 
Ventures, M/C Venture Partners, and Osborne Capital.
	http://www.harvardnet.com
	
	
	Advice Site Exp.com Changes Strategy, Cuts 15% of Staff
	mail this story? top
	
	MENLO PARK, Calif. (VENTUREWIRE) -- Exp.com, a Web site where users can post 
a question and get expert advice, said it is laying off 15% of its staff, or 
17 emmployees, as a result of its change in business strategy to focus more 
on the business-to-business market. The company said it will offer similar 
services to businesses, providing infrastructure that will enable businesses 
to offer their own network of experts or use Exp.com's list of experts. The 
company said it continues to hire, specifically in sales and engineering 
departments, and plans to be profitable without additional funding. Exp.com 
is backed by Ask Jeeves, MeVC Draper Fisher Jurvetson, Bessmer Venture 
Partners, CMGI@Ventures, Maveron, Bowman Capital, J. & W. Seligman, and 
Oracle Ventures.
	http://www.exp.com
	
	
	@Viso Will No Longer Fund Jewelry Retailer Diamond.com 
	mail this story? top
	
	FT. LAUDERDALE, Fla. (VENTUREWIRE) -- Diamond.com, a diamond and jewelry 
retail site said it will not receive any new investments from French 
incubator @Viso as  planned.  @Viso is a joint venture between Vivendi and 
Softbank, aimed at helping US Internet companies gain market entry into 
continental Europe. Earlier this week Softbank said @Viso will not be making 
new investments. According to a diamond.com spokesperson, both companies are 
"resizing." @Viso has invested $2 million in Diamond.com to date. Odimo, 
majority owned by Softbank Capital Partners and The Steinmetz Diamond Group, 
purchased Diamond.com in May. Diamond.com closed a round of funding led by 
Softbank last week which also included The Steinmetz Group, STI Ventures, 
Data Investments, and Lipton Group. 
	http://www.diamond.com
	
	
	divine interVentures Takes Back $10 Million Commitment
	mail this story? top
	
	CHICAGO (VENTUREWIRE) -- Divine interVentures, the publicly traded 
information technology holding company, said it withdrew its $10 million 
commitmeent to Skyscraper Ventures, a seed and early-stage venture fund. 
Skyscraper's remaining partner, Mesirow Financial, said it will focus on 
finding a suitable replacement or if not, find a new investment vehicle to 
continue Skyscraper's investment strategy. In a statement, divine's Paul 
Humenansky, president and COO said, "We continue to support high-tech 
development in the Chicago area, but believe in light of current market 
conditions we must dedicate our efforts and capital toward maximizing the 
value of our existing associated companies and to meet our planned investment 
level." In November, divine let go of 43% of its staff.
	http://www.divineinterventures.com
	
	
	CarsDirect.com Pulls IPO Citing Market Conditions
	mail this story? top
	
	NEW YORK (VENTUREWIRE) -- CarsDirect.com, the online auto dealer which raised 
over $300 million in venture capital funding, pulled its IPO. In a lettter to 
the SEC the company said, "it is not in the best interest of the company's 
stockholders to proceed with the offering under the current volatile market 
conditions." CarsDirect.com is backed by investors including idealab!, along 
with Foundation Capital, Goldman Sachs Group, MSD Capital, Primedia Ventures, 
UnitedAuto Group and Penske Automotive Group, and a number of other investors.
	http://www.carsdirect.com
	
	
