	Global E-Library Network BiblioMondo.com Launches
	mail this story? top
	
	PHILADELPHIA (VENTUREWIRE) -- BiblioMondo.com, a global electronic library 
network announced it has launched. The company was formed after Best-Seller, 
aa software company, acquired the European Software Maker ALS International, 
and renamed it BiblioMondo.com. The acquisition was funded by Investissement 
Desjardins, The Royal Bank of Canada, TechnoCap of Montreal, and an 
individual European investor. BiblioMondo.com has network nodes in London, 
Paris, Cologne, Amsterdam, Philadelphia, and Montreal.    
	http://www.bibliomondo.com
	
	
	Tech Firm Telaric to Launch Incubator Services in January
	mail this story? top
	
	MEQUON, Wis. (VENTUREWIRE) -- Telaric, which has developed its own technology 
and created spin-off companies CartaNova and Vigilo to commercialize its 
teechnology, said as of the first of the year it will be offering high tech 
incubator services to companies in the medical electronics, medical 
information technology, and business information technology areas. Telaric 
said it will provide financial advice, facilities, equipment, and 
administrative support. To date, Telaric has been funded by founders and 
partners, but is in the process of raising a round of external financing. 
Telephone 414-803-8182.
	
	
