	Brightstar and IncuVest Form Strategic Alliance
	mail this story? top
	
	LONDON (VENTUREWIRE) -- Brightstar, an incubator owned by British 
Telecommunications (BT), said it is creating an alliance with incuVest, which 
devvelops and operates technology companies. The two companies will look for 
new business opportunities and technologies to establish. The company said 
there will be an undisclosed equity exchange as part of the deal. incuVEst 
will have 60 to 70 employees at BT. IncuVest opened a U.K. office in October. 
	http://www.btbrightstar.com
