	Interfaith Web Site Beliefnet.com Acquires CharityCounts.com
	mail this story? top
	
	NEW YORK (VENTUREWIRE) -- Beliefnet.com, a multifaith Web site providing 
information, advice, and news, said it acquired CharityCounts.com, a Web 
sitte that includes information on several nonprofit organizations. Beliefnet 
will use CharityCounts technology to enable its users to make cash donations 
and participate in daily auctions, the proceeds of which will be donated to 
the charity of their choice. Gregg Greenberg, former chief executive officer 
of CharityCounts, will oversee the integration of the two companies' 
platforms and has not decided whether or not to stay with the company. 
CharityCounts was funded by individual investors. Beliefnet was funded by 
Highland Capital Partners, Primus Venture Partners, Blue Chip Venture, Zero 
Stage Capital, and the Trump Group.
	http://www.beliefnet.com
	http://www.charitycounts.com
	
	
	FilmTrust Acquires IFILM Software Assets for Equity Stake
	mail this story? top
	
	HOLLYWOOD, Calif. (VENTUREWIRE) -- IFILM, a film portal and directory, and 
Filmtrust, an enterprise ASP for the entertainment industry, said they have 
formed  a strategic agreement. Under the terms of the deal, Filmtrust will 
acquire IFILM's key software assets including Productionpro, Locationpro, and 
Jobpro. IFILM will provide Filmtrust with promotional and marketing support 
and consulting to help bring the tools to market. IFILM will receive a 
preferred equity position in Filmtrust for its contributions to the 
co-venture, which will be branded under the Filmtrust name. Filmtrust was 
formed in February 1999 as a joint venture with Digital Commerce Corporation 
(DCC), a creator of e-commerce services for government and industry. The 
venture was launched through an alliance between Filmtrust and Entertainment 
Partners (EP), a developer and marketer of entertainment industry production 
accounting software and services. IFILM's backers include Eastman Kodak, 
Liberty Digital, Shamrock Capital Advisors, Sony, and Vulcan Ventures. 
	http://www.filmtrust.com
	http://www.ifilm.com
	
	
	Inustry B2B Dairy.com and INC2inc Merge to Form Momentx
	mail this story? top
	
	DALLAS (VENTUREWIRE) -- Dairy.com, a business-to-business exchange for the 
dairy industry, and INC2inc Technologies, an online market and supply chhain 
service for the food and beverage industry, announced their merger and the 
formation of a parent company, Momentx. Momentx will be headquartered in 
Dallas. Gregg Engles, chairman of the board and CEO of Suiza Foods, will 
serve as chairman of the board. Scott Sexton, president of INC2inc, will 
serve as president. INC2inc's 45 employees will become employees of Momentx. 
Dairy.com was founded in July by eight dairy industry organizations including 
Dairy Farmers of America, The Dannon Company, Dreyer's Grand Ice Cream, Kraft 
Foods, Land O'Lakes, Leprino Foods, Schreiber Foods, and Suiza Foods. 
Dairy.com plans to launch its first release in the first quarter of 2001 with 
live trading of commodities including milk and cream. INC2Inc is backed by 
Spyglass Equities.  
	http://www.dairy.com
	http://www.inc2inc.ocm
	
	
	Media Ad Sales Site BuyMedia Acquires REP-PAK Media Systems
	mail this story? top
	
	BURLINGAME, Calif. (VENTUREWIRE) -- BuyMedia, a provider of technology that 
enables media buying and selling, said it signed a letter of intent to 
acquire REP--PAK Media Systems, a Canadian broadcast sales software provider. 
The acquisition is the BuyMedia's first acquisition outside the U.S. 
REP-PAK's management positions are yet to be decided. In September, BuyMedia 
acquired the TvScan and Cablescan divisions of Tapscan, which provides sales 
software for TV and cable industries. BuyMedia is funded by Internet Capital 
